# GitHub Personal Access Token (used for the "Last Updated" column).
#
# 1. Visit https://github.com/settings/tokens
# 2. Click "Generate new token" → "Generate new token (classic)"
# 3. Note: name it "norns-scraper" or similar
# 4. Expiration: pick whatever you're comfortable with
# 5. Scopes: just "public_repo" (or none — only public repos are queried)
# 6. Click "Generate token" and copy the token
# 7. Save this file as "gh.api" (drop the .example) and replace the line below
#    with just the token (no quotes, no newlines)
#
# In GitHub Actions: this file is NOT used. The workflow pipes the auto-provided
# `secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN` to the scraper as the GITHUB_TOKEN env var.
#
# Without a token, the scraper falls back to unauthenticated GitHub (60 req/hr),
# which means "Last Updated" will only populate ~17% of rows per run.
ghp_REPLACE_THIS_WITH_YOUR_TOKEN
